"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390921","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-07-24","<p /> <p>Over the last Parliament, the Statements of New Regulation set out the regulations introduced and removed, and the costs and savings this achieved for business. The Ninth Statement of New Regulation gives the overall account of measures introduced 2010- 2015 and their costs and savings. This can be found on the Gov.UK website.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390921/answer",,,,,"7862","2015-07-24T14:56:13.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390921/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390921/answer",,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-07-17","Business: Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many regulations were (a) introduced and (b) removed in each financial year from 2010-11 to 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","7861"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390922","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-07-24","<p>Over the last Parliament, the Statements of New Regulation set out the regulations introduced and removed, and the costs and savings this achieved for business. The Ninth Statement of New Regulation gives the overall account of measures introduced 2010- 2015 and their costs and savings. This can be found on the Gov.UK website.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390922/answer",,,,,"7861","2015-07-24T14:56:13.723Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390922/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390922/answer",,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-07-17","Business: Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what estimate he has made of the cost of (a) introducing and (b) removing regulations in each financial year from 2010-11 to 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","7862"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390923","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-07-27","<p>My Rt hon Friend the Prime Minister is leading a whole-of-government approach to increase UK exports. An Exports Implementation Taskforce has been established to monitor and drive delivery. Chaired by the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, the Taskforce meets every two weeks and reports to the Prime Minister and Cabinet quarterly.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390923/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-27T13:44:01.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390923/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390923/answer",,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-07-17","Exports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps he is taking to implement a whole-of-Government approach to export support: and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","7863"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390924","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-27","<p>The use of equipment and weapons supplied to the Saudis is an operational matter for the Saudi military authorities. The Saudis have assured us that British-supplied munitions will be used in compliance with international humanitarian law and we continue to engage with them on these assurances.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390924/answer",,,,,"7824","2015-07-27T13:48:29.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390924/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390924/answer",,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-17","Yemen: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, on which dates and in what locations British precision-guided missiles, licensed for export, have been used in the current conflict in Yemen.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","7820"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390925","Cabinet Office","false","2015-07-21","<p>The 2015 National Security Strategy, informed by the National Security Risk Assessment, is considering a wide range of risks including those to our economic and financial security.</p>","West Dorset","Mr Oliver Letwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390925/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-21T17:18:13.07Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390925/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Letwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390925/answer",,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-07-17","National Security","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, if the Government will assess the vulnerability of the UK to economic and financial warfare when developing the National Security Strategy.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","7870"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390926","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-24","<p>This government considers the resilience of the financial sector to a range of security threats and natural hazards. While responsibility for the resilience of the financial sector is primarily for firms themselves, the government continues to support measures to strengthen the resilience of the sector, and in particular its critical systems, working closely with the Bank of England (BoE) the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA), wider government and the sector.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390926/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-24T08:16:42.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390926/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390926/answer",,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-17","Financial Services: Terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the vulnerability of the financial system to terrorist actions; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","7869"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390927","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-24","<p>The EU Markets in Financial Instruments Directive (MiFID 2) will from 3 January 2017 bring in a new regime for the regulation of commodity derivatives, which will include limits on the size of positions a person can take and reporting obligations.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390927/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-24T08:14:27.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390927/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390927/answer",,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-17","Commodity Markets: Oil","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps he has taken to reduce speculation in and improve the transparency and supervision of the oil futures market; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","7871"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390928","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-27","<p>Tables were placed in the library which provide information on awards made under Section 64 of the Health and Public Health Act 1968 for the financial years 2010-11 to 2014-15 in response to HL5149 answered on 5<sup>th</sup> March 2015.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Treasury reviews value for money as part of the assessment process for each grant prior to its award. The full assessment includes consideration of the proposal against HM Treasury standard business case criteria which includes a Strategic Case, Economic Case, Financial Case, Commercial Case and Project Governance.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Each grant application is assessed on its own merits and approval is only given where it is expected the grant will provide value for money.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In October 2014 HMT agreed to a deemed consent arrangement for grants under £1,000,000 whereby the Department of Health Director of Group Finance has consent to approve grants up to this value unless they are novel, contentious or repercussive. The Department of Health agreed to provide details of grants approved under this arrangement on a regular basis.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Under this authority Treasury approval can be deemed in respect of grants or loans to Voluntary and Community Sector (VCS) organisations where the Department of Health is able to confirm that:</p><p> </p><ul><li><p>The grant or loan is affordable with DH’s settlement;</p></li><li><p>The grant or loan represents best value for money;</p></li><li><p>The grant team has reviewed the case under the normal section 64 business case criteria.</p><p> </p></li></ul><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390928/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-27T12:33:21.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390928/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390928/answer",,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-17","Treasury: Grants","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the value was of grants approved by his Department under section 64 of the Health Services and Public Health Act 1968 in each of the last five years; and what assessment his Department has made of the value for money and effectiveness with which funding so awarded has been spent.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","7826"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390929","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-27","<p>Officials within the Health Spending team have responsibility for providing HM Treasury approval for grants made under the powers of Section 64 of the Health Services and Public Health Act 1968. The Chief Secretary to the Treasury has overall responsibility for the decisions made by the Health Spending team.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HMT officials review an assessment of the proposal against HM Treasury standard business case criteria which includes a Strategic Case, Economic Case, Financial Case, Commercial Case and Project Governance.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In October 2014 HMT agreed to a deemed consent arrangement for grants under £1,000,000 whereby the Director of Group Finance at the Department of Health has consent to approve grants up to this value unless they are novel, contentious or repercussive. The Department of Health agreed to provide details of grants approved under this arrangement on a regular basis.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Under this authority Treasury approval can be deemed in respect of grants or loans to Voluntary and Community Sector (VCS) organisations where the Department of Health is able to confirm that:</p><p> </p><ul><li><p>The grant or loan is affordable with DH’s settlement;</p></li><li><p>The grant or loan represents best value for money;</p></li><li><p>The grant team has reviewed the case under the normal section 64 business case criteria.</p><p> </p></li></ul><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390929/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-27T10:22:50.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390929/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390929/answer",,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-17","Treasury: Grants","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the job title is of the (a) official and (b) Minister in his Department with responsibility for approving grants made under section 64 of the Health Services and Public Health Act 1968; against what criteria such grants are awarded; and what the process is for considering applications for such grants.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","7827"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390930","Department of Health","false","2015-07-22","<p>The impact of the new National Living Wage on local authority finances will be considered during the Spending Review as part of an overall assessment of spending pressures on local authorities.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390930/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-22T14:57:34.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390930/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390930/answer",,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-17","Carers: Living Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate his Department has made of the additional annual costs to councils of paying the National Living Wage to care workers employed by private firms to provide adult social care services for local authorities from April 2016.","false","Biography information for Mr Clive Betts","Sheffield South East","Mr Clive Betts","7771"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390931","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-24","<p>Total Machine Games Duty (MGD) receipts for the year ending 31 March 2015 are £565 million. This includes, from 1 March 2015, MGD payable at the higher rate (but this amount is not identified separately). The higher rate is forecast to raise an additional £75 million a year.</p><p> </p><p>(<a href="https://www.uktradeinfo.com/Statistics/Pages/TaxAndDutybulletins.aspx" target="_blank">https://www.uktradeinfo.com/Statistics/Pages/TaxAndDutybulletins.aspx</a>)</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390931/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-24T12:05:39.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390931/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390931/answer",,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-17","Gaming Machines: Tax Yields","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much revenue has been raised from the fixed-odds betting terminals tax.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","7798"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390932","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-09-08","<p>We encourage all beekeepers to register the location of their hives on the National Bee Unit’s Beebase system. However it is not possible to provide an accurate figure for hives located on local authority land.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390932/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-08T11:24:14.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390932/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390932/answer",,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-07-17","Department for Communities and Local Government: Bees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many bee hives are sited on land and buildings owned by local authorities in the North West of England.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mr Mark Hendrick","7843"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390933","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-09-08","<p>This information is not held centrally and would be held by each local authority.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390933/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-08T11:32:32.583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390933/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390933/answer",,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-07-17","Animal Welfare: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how much each district and unitary council in the North West of England obtained in animal licensing fees in 2014.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mr Mark Hendrick","7846"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390934","Department for Education","false","2015-07-22","<p>Our statutory guidance, ‘Planning Transition to Adulthood for Care Leavers<em>’</em> sets out local authorities’ responsibilities when care leavers are placed out of area. In these circumstances, the placing local authority must remain in close contact and take responsibility for planning the young person’s transition to adulthood. The guidance explains that local authorities should work together with relevant agencies such as health and adult social care services when planning a young person’s transition to adulthood.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Where a care leaver is placed in custody, pathway planning must continue. The young person must be visited on a regular basis by a personal adviser from the placing authority. It is good practice for the personal adviser to carry out a review of the pathway plan at least a month before release in order to give sufficient time for pre-release planning. This should include plans for the care leaver to move into suitable accommodation, with the right kind of support, on release from custody.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>A copy of the guidance is available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/397649/CA1989_Transitions_guidance.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/397649/CA1989_Transitions_guidance.pdf</a></p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390934/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-22T11:46:55.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390934/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390934/answer",,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-07-17","Children in Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will introduce legislative proposals to place a legal responsibility on local authorities to notify their neighbouring authorities when they place 16 to 21 year olds leaving (a) care and (b) young offender institutions in that area.","false","Biography information for Julian Knight","Solihull","Julian Knight","7808"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390935","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-22","<p>Latest published statistics show that 2,570 families with children were in bed and breakfast style accommodation in England as at 31 March 2015. Of these households, 920 had been in bed and breakfast style accommodation for more than six weeks (50 of which were pending review).</p><p> </p><p><br>The statistics are not compiled on the basis of parliamentary constituencies.</p><p><br>The law is clear that bed and breakfast accommodation should be used to house homeless families only in an emergency, and then for no longer than six weeks. Practice varies significantly across the country with just 5% of councils accounting for 80% of the total number of families stuck in these unacceptable conditions for more than 6 weeks. We provided funding in 2013-14 so that authorities could develop innovative and sustainable approaches to tackle this issue.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390935/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-22T15:59:55.703Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390935/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390935/answer",,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-07-17","Bed and Breakfast Accommodation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many families with children living in bed and breakfast accommodation have been so accommodated for more than six weeks; and how many families with children live in bed and breakfast accommodation in (a) each parliamentary constituency in the East Midlands and (b) England.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","7855"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390936","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-22","<p>Statistics on house building completions by tenure in each local authority district are published in the Department's live tables 253 (annual) and 253a (quarterly), which are available at the following link.</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/live-tables-on-house-building" target="_blank">http://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/live-tables-on-house-building</a></p><p> </p><p>More comprehensive statistics on affordable housing completions are published in the Department’s live tables 1006, 1006a, 1007 and 1008, which are available at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/live-tables-on-affordable-housing-supply" target="_blank">http://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/live-tables-on-affordable-housing-supply</a></p><p> </p><p>These statistics include both newly built housing and acquisitions.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390936/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-22T15:58:04.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390936/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390936/answer",,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-07-17","Housing: Cumbria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many (a) homes and (b) affordable homes have been built in each local authority area in Cumbria in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","7777"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390937","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-27","<p>Pursuant to the Answer of 15 July 2015 to Question 6223 the organisations which were awarded money for integration projects and activities are shown in the attached table.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390937/answer","PQ 7872.docx","PQ 7872.docx","Table of Integration Projects ","Table of Integration Projects ",,"2015-07-27T12:15:19.73Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390937/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390937/answer",,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-07-17","Community Relations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 15 July 2015 to Question 6223, which groups were awarded money for integration projects.","false","Biography information for Liam Byrne","Birmingham, Hodge Hill","Liam Byrne","7872"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390938","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-27","<p>My Department monitors integration projects to ensure they deliver the agreed outcomes and milestones set out in their grant agreement. For example, our investment of £8 million since 2011 in the Near Neighbours programme has supported over 924 local projects that bring different faith and ethnic groups together, benefitting over 650,000 local people; while funding of £10 million has established over 600 new cadet units providing opportunities for over 11,000 young people.<br><br></p><p> </p><p> </p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390938/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-27T12:11:11.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390938/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390938/answer",,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-07-17","Community Relations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 15 July 2015 to Question 6223, what measures he has used to assess the results and performance of the £50 million invested through the integration strategy.","false","Biography information for Liam Byrne","Birmingham, Hodge Hill","Liam Byrne","7873"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390939","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-21","<p>The commencement order bringing in the provisions on retaliatory evictions was made on 27 March 2015. It is titled, the Deregulation Act 2015 (Commencement No 1 and Transitional and Saving Provisions) Order 2015, and available at: <a href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2015/994/contents/made" target="_blank">http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2015/994/contents/made</a>. Its provisions have effect from 1 October 2015.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390939/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-21T17:00:47.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390939/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390939/answer",,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-07-17","Private Rented Housing: Evictions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, with reference to sections 33 to 41 of the Deregulation Act 2015, when he expects to make the commencement order on retaliatory evictions.","false","Biography information for Dr Roberta Blackman-Woods","City of Durham","Dr Roberta Blackman-Woods","7875"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390940","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-07-29","<p>The Government remains committed to seeing an improvement in the provision of access services for video-on-demand (VoD) services and will continue to monitor progress. If the Authority for Television on Demand’s (ATVOD's) 2015 annual survey of VoD Services indicates that significant progress has not been made then, as stated in the Connectivity, Content and Consumers Paper (July 2013), we will consider legislation in 2016. The Department for Culture, Media and Sport does not have policy responsibility for sensory loss for new social media.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390940/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-29T15:43:08.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390940/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390940/answer",,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-17","Digital Technology: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps he is taking to ensure that people with sensory loss can share in the benefits of (a) on-demand television services and (b) new social media.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","7874"
