,230,847</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011/2012</p></td><td><p>10,221,762</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/2013</p></td><td><p>12,723,793</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/2014</p></td><td><p>10,780,211</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/2015</p></td><td><p>21,822,545</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong> 61,779,158</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong>England total awards (both Exchequer and National Lottery investment, and all investment in National Governing Bodies)</strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Financial Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total (£)</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010/2011</p></td><td><p>173,624,416</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011/2012</p></td><td><p>235,770,284</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/2013</p></td><td><p>199,462,828</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/2014</p></td><td><p>402,635,902</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/2015</p></td><td><p>312,592,975</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Grand Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong> 1,324,086,405</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p>These are the most up-to-date figures. Awards are updated each quarter with new commitments, decommitments and adjustments. Delivery postcodes are also, on occasion, updated to be more accurate. This is why there are differences in the figures for the PQ above and the answer given to PQ 169026 from Gloria De Piero MP of 8 October 2013.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390941/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-28T15:01:19.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390941/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390941/answer",,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-17","Sports: Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how much his Department has spent on sport in (a) Ashfield constituency, (b) Nottinghamshire, (c) East Midlands and (d) England in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","7849"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390942","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-07-28","<p>A betting premises licence issued under the Gambling Act 2005 authorises its holder to make up to 4 gaming machines available for use. This entitlement is limited to gaming machines terminals which fall within sub-categories B2 (what we commonly think of when we refer to FOBTs), B3 and B4, and categories C and D.</p><p><br> <br></p><p>Industry data shows that the constituency of Copeland ha for all categories of gaming machines:</p><p> </p><p>54 terminals in 2015</p><p>50 terminals in 2014</p><p>49 terminals in 2013</p><p>46 terminals in 2012</p><p> </p><p><br> There are no figures for 2011.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390942/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-28T15:02:23.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390942/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390942/answer",,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-17","Gaming Machines: Copeland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many fixed-odds betting terminals there were in Copeland constituency in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","7797"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390943","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-07-28","<p>The total amount of prize money distributed in horseracing over the past 5 years is as follows:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Calendar Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2010</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Amount (£m)</strong></p></td><td><p>98.96</p></td><td><p>93.89</p></td><td><p>97.78</p></td><td><p>114.2</p></td><td><p>123.2</p></td><td><p>130.8 (estimate)</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><em>Source: BHA Fact Book 2014 for 2010-2013 inclusive; BHA press notice of 14 January 2015 for 2014 and 2015</em></p><p>Notes:</p><p>a) Prize money comes from three main sources – the Levy Board, Racecourses (including sponsor contributions) and Owners (via entry fees).</p><p>b) The sport of horseracing is organised by calendar year.</p><p> </p><p>Total yield in the past 5 financial years from betting operators via the Levy Board, comprising statutory Levy payments and contributions made voluntarily, is as follows:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Financial Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2010/11</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011/12</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012/13</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013/14</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014/15</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Amount (£m)</strong></p></td><td><p>59.9</p></td><td><p>74.7</p></td><td><p>74.3</p></td><td><p>78.0</p></td><td><p>71.8</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><em>Source: Horserace Betting Levy Board</em></p><p>Notes:</p><p>a) Levy Schemes follow the financial year.</p><p>b) Offshore remote operators do not pay Levy unless they choose to do so through voluntary arrangements.</p><p> </p><p>The Department holds no annual breakdowns of information about betting industry payments to racing by way of media rights. <em>The Economic Impact of British Racing 2013</em> (Deloitte) notes that relevant media companies received a total income of £153m in 2012 compared with £104m in 2008 (p.12). After deducting media companies’ operating costs, £88m of this was paid to the racecourses in 2012 (2008: £57m).</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Department holds no annual breakdowns of information about betting industry payments to racing by way of sponsorship. The total amount of sponsorship received by racing in 2012, from all sources, amounted to £38.6m, of which £31m went to racecourses. 41% of sponsored races were sponsored by betting companies (up from 37% in 2005). The total prize money of those races was £31.8m, but not all of this can be attributed to contributions from the betting industry (<em>The Economic Impact of British Racing 2013</em> p.44).</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390943/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-28T15:04:39.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390943/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390943/answer",,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-17","Horse Racing: Prize Money","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what information his Department holds on the total prize money dispersed in horse racing in each of the last five years; and what estimate he has made of how much the betting industry has contributed to horse racing through (a) levy payments, (b) media rights and (c) sponsorship in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","7767"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390944","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-27","<p>I receive regular briefings on UK operations, including surveillance flights, over Syria. When necessary, I am informed of the actions of UK personnel embedded with other coalition forces.</p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390944/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-27T13:48:01.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390944/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390944/answer",,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-17","Syria: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what reports he has received since 30 April 2013 on involvement of British military personnel in actions in Syria.","false","Biography information for Brendan O'Hara","Argyll and Bute","Brendan O'Hara","7791"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390945","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-27","<p>Yes. My predecessor and I authorised a small number of UK personnel embedded with US and Canadian forces to deploy with their units on operations in Iraq and Syria.</p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390945/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-27T13:47:26.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390945/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390945/answer",,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-17","Syria: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether he was informed of the deployment of British military personnel in military action in Syria prior to the debate on Britain and International Security on 2 July 2015.","false","Biography information for Brendan O'Hara","Argyll and Bute","Brendan O'Hara","7841"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390946","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-24","<p>No decisions have yet been taken by the Government on a wider post- Afghanistan review. We have been learning the tactical lessons of our operations in Afghanistan throughout the campaign.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390946/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-24T11:13:23.75Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390946/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390946/answer",,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-17","Afghanistan: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 7 July 2015 to Question 5927, if he will commission a lessons learned post-Afghanistan review to inform future military strategy.","true","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","7772"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390947","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-27","<p>Personnel from all three Services have been involved in Operation SHADER, the name given to UK operations to counter-ISIL in Iraq and Syria. The UK has permission to fly manned Intelligence, surveillance and reconnaissance aircraft, as well as Reaper unmanned aircraft, over Syria.</p><p>In addition, a number of UK personnel are embedded with our coalition partners; these personnel are operating as members of those nations' military.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390947/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-27T13:46:12.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390947/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390947/answer",,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-17","Syria: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many operations British armed forces personnel have been involved in Syria since 30 August 2013; and from which branch of the armed forces each such personnel was deployed.","false","Biography information for Brendan O'Hara","Argyll and Bute","Brendan O'Hara","7778"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390948","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-27","<p>None.</p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390948/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-27T13:44:15.52Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390948/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390948/answer",,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-17","Syria: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many British combat aircraft have been deployed in Syria since 30 August 2013.","false","Biography information for Brendan O'Hara","Argyll and Bute","Brendan O'Hara","7779"
