<p> </p><p><em>Source:</em> consultant-led referral to treatment waiting times, NHS England</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><em>Notes: </em></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><ol start="1" type="1"><li>London is defined as London Strategic Health Authority to March 2013 and London Area Team from April 2013.</li><li>The information is published by National Health Service commissioning area (primary care trusts (PCTs) to March 2013 and clinical commissioning groups (CCGs) from April 2013) and not by local authority or parliamentary constituency. Islington is therefore defined as Islington PCT to March 2013 and NHS Islington CCG from April 2013.</li><li>Referral to treatment waiting times for patients whose wait ended during the month with an inpatient or day case admission for treatment.</li><li>Referral to treatment waiting times for patients whose wait ended during the month for reasons other than an inpatient or day case admission for treatment (e.g. started treatment in an outpatient setting).</li><li>Responsibility for the commissioning of consultant-led sexual health services was transferred to local authorities on 1 April 2013. This means that data is not consistent over the period and is likely to have had most effect on the median waits for non-admitted patients.</li></ol><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391001/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-23T14:29:57.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391001/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391001/answer",,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-17","Hospitals: Waiting Lists","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the average waiting time was between referral to secondary care and the beginning of treatment in (a) England, (b) London, (c) the London Borough of Islington and (d) Islington South and Finsbury constituency in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","7784"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391002","Department of Health","false","2015-07-22","<p>The Department does not collect this information.</p><p> </p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391002/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-22T14:30:40.09Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391002/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391002/answer",,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-17","General Practitioners: Overseas Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate he has made of the number of UK-trained GPs who opted to practice overseas on completing their training in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","7785"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391003","Department of Health","false","2015-07-23","<p>An application for grant funding from Action on Smoking and Health has not been refused in the last five years.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391003/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-23T14:45:06.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391003/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391003/answer",,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-17","Action on Smoking and Health: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether any application for grant funding from Action on Smoking and Health has been refused in the last five years; and what the date and reasons for such refusal were in each such case.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","7806"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391004","Department of Health","false","2015-07-23","<p>Information is not available on the number of patients who have not seen a dentist in the last two years because the Department does not collect information on private dental treatment.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391004/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-23T09:59:40.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391004/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391004/answer",,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-17","Dental Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many people and what proportion of patients in each region of England have not seen a dentist in the last two years.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","7810"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391005","Department of Health","false","2015-07-22","<p>No estimate has been made of the number of male and female general practitioners who left the profession, for reasons other than retirement, in each of the last 10 years.</p><p> </p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391005/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-22T14:33:20.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391005/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391005/answer",,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-17","General Practitioners: Resignations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate he has made of the number of (a) male and (b) female GPs who left the profession, for reasons other than retirement, in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","7786"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391006","Department of Health","false","2015-07-22","<p>This information is not collected centrally.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In terms of the total for England, numbers of new contracts agreed with GP practices is not collected nationally.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391006/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-22T13:59:18.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391006/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391006/answer",,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-17","General Practitioners: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many new (a) General Medical Services, (b) Personal Medical Services and (c) Alternative Provider Medical Services contracts were agreed with GP practices in (i) England, (ii) London, (iii) the London Borough of Islington and (iv) Islington South and Finsbury constituency in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","7783"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391007","Department of Health","false","2015-07-22","<p>Health services are a devolved matter with each United Kingdom country responsible for ensuring they have a workforce that is equipped to deliver high quality patient care. However, the four UK countries are committed to working together to ensure, where appropriate, Workforce Education and Training policies are aligned.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>General practice trainees in England are already required to undertake 18 month placements in general practice as part of their postgraduate specialty training. Currently, general practices that provide training do not contribute to that trainee’s salary, which is funded by Health Education England. General practices are also given a general practitioner trainers grant to contribute towards the cost of training.</p><p> </p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391007/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-22T15:16:14.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391007/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391007/answer",,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-17","General Practitioners: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what plans he has to monitor the introduction in Wales of an 18-month training placement for general practice during which trainees will be salaried directly by the Welsh NHS; and whether he plans to introduce such measures in England.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","7787"
