"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390671","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-21","<p>I refer the Rt. Hon member to the Written Ministerial Statement on the Office of Tax Simplification published on 21 July 2015</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390671/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-21T13:49:29.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390671/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390671/answer",,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-16","Office of Tax Simplification","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what additional responsibilities he intends to give to the Office for Tax Simplification; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","7581"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390672","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-21","<p>Employer investment in skills has been a problem since the 1990s. The new apprenticeship levy will mean that firms that are committed to training will be able to get back more than the put in. Further details will be set out at the spending review.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390672/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-21T16:05:26.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390672/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390672/answer",,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-16","Apprentices: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, at what level he intends to set the apprenticeship levy; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","7579"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390673","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-23","<p>Since 2010 UKTI has more than doubled the number of businesses it helps on an annual basis, whilst UKEF has provided £14.5bn of support for exports since 2010-11.The government’s productivity plan set out further steps to build stronger trading links with emerging markets, especially China, India and Brazil, and to mobilise the whole of government behind exporting, working alongside a more effective UKTI and better export finance. The government’s commitment to eliminate the budget deficit, combined with monetary activism, will also support a narrowing of the current account deficit.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390673/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-23T14:51:25.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390673/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390673/answer",,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-16","Balance of Payments","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps he is taking to reduce the current account deficit; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","7624"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390674","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-24","<p>As the changes to maintenance arrangements will come into effect for the academic year 2016-17, they will be factored into the budget for the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills which will be set at the forthcoming Spending Review. The Barnett Formula will be applied to this settlement in the usual way.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Should the Welsh Government choose to offer students from Wales maintenance loans on a similar basis, the Treasury will make available a proportionate level of cover.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390674/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-24T12:09:45.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390674/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390674/answer",,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-16","Students: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what Barnett consequential will accrue to Wales as a result of the planned saving of £2.5 billion of the decision to replace maintenance grants with maintenance loans for students in England.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Edwards","Carmarthen East and Dinefwr","Jonathan Edwards","7618"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390675","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-21","<p>The information is not available as HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) do not record the time taken between receipt and response for each piece of correspondence about inheritance tax.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HMRC aims to respond to 80% of general inheritance tax correspondence within 15 working days. If the correspondence is a full inheritance tax return a response will take longer because of routine compliance checks.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390675/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-21T16:12:33.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390675/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390675/answer",,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-16","Inheritance Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the average length of time is between the date of receipt by HM Revenue and Customs of correspondence about inheritance tax liability and a response being given.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","7586"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390676","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-22","<p>The Government has made a firm commitment to our Northern Powerhouse initiative which is inclusive of the whole of the North of England and the North East. We have made a series of investments across transport, infrastructure, skills, and business enterprise, and detailed additional measures to support the region at Summer Budget. In addition, the Chancellor recently announced that the government has begun discussions with the North East Combined Authority on a potential devolution deal, including plans for creating a directly-elected mayor, in return for a transfer of powers to the region.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390676/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-22T14:59:47.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390676/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390676/answer",,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-16","Regional Planning and Development: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps he is taking to include cities in the North East in the Northern Powerhouse initiative; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","7614"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390677","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-23","<p>The Government has driven a wide ranging programme of reforms to help Small and Medium Sized Enterprises to gain access to finance and to support competition in the SME lending market.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government introduced the Current Account Switch Service which is a free-to-use service for customers that makes it easier, quicker and more reliable for customers to switch banks. At Budget 2015 the scheme was extended to include 99% of SMEs.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>This year the Government will lay final legislation requiring major UK banks both to share SME credit information with other lenders and to offer to share the details of SMEs rejected for a loan with online platforms that can match them to alternative finance providers. Alongside these reforms, the British Business Bank is increasing and diversifying the supply of finance available to SMEs, and aims to facilitate up to £10 billion of finance by 2019.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390677/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-23T14:50:40.243Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390677/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390677/answer",,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-16","Business: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps he is taking to improve competition in small and medium-sized enterprise bank lending; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","7615"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390678","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-23","<p>This is a matter for the Prudential Regulation Authority (PRA), which is operationally independent from Government.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The question has been passed on to the PRA. The PRA will reply directly to the Member by letter. A copy of the letter will be placed in the Library of the House.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390678/answer",,,,,"7642","2015-07-23T14:49:19.21Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390678/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390678/answer",,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-16","Banks: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, which firms have relinquished a banking licence in the last 30 years.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","7617"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390679","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-21","<p>The Government is making changes to Tax Credits and Universal Credit which will help put welfare spending on a more sustainable path. That means more emphasis on support to hardworking families on low incomes by reducing income tax through increases in the personal allowance and increasing wages, than on topping up low wages through tax credits.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HMT has published distributional analysis information on the impact of the Summer Budget 2015 which includes the effect of tax credit and other welfare measures on households. This information can be found here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/443229/PU1822_Distributional_Analysis.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/443229/PU1822_Distributional_Analysis.pdf</a></p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390679/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-21T16:00:57.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390679/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390679/answer",,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-16","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many claimants will receive a net reduction in (a) tax credits, (b) disability living allowance and (c) housing support as a result of measures in the 2015 Summer Budget.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","7561"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390680","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-22","<p>Further details will be announced at the Spending Review following a formal engagement with business. Most importantly, firms that are committed to training will be able to get back more than they put in.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390680/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-22T15:11:45.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390680/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390680/answer",,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-16","Apprentices: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many companies will be required to pay the apprenticeship levy; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","7551"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390681","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-22","<p>We intend to either remove or significantly reduce the Network Grant by re-routing Government support via franchised train operating companies, which will pay correspondingly higher track access charges to Network Rail for using the network. This change will not affect the overall level of support Government will be providing to rail.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>This new approach will ensure that Network Rail focuses firmly on the needs of train operators, and through them, customers.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Working with the Office of Rail and Road, we intend this change to take effect from the start of Control Period 6 (April 2019). We will be consulting with industry on the details.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390681/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-22T09:41:22.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390681/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390681/answer",,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-16","Network Rail: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what changes he intends to make to the funding arrangements for Network Rail; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","7552"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390682","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-24","<p>This Government has made a long term commitment to science capital funding which has risen to £1.1 billion in 2015-16 and will increase in line with inflation out to 2020-21.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Future funding allocations for science resource funding, including medical research, will be determined at the forthcoming Spending Review.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390682/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-24T12:08:33.783Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390682/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390682/answer",,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-16","Science: Research","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether he intends to (a) maintain, (b) increase or (c) decrease scientific and medical research spending in real terms over the next (i) one year and (ii) five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","7611"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390683","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-21","<p>The Government is making changes to Tax Credits and Universal Credit which will help put welfare spending on a more sustainable path. That means more emphasis on support to hardworking families on low incomes by reducing income tax through increases in the personal allowance and increasing wages, than on topping up low wages through tax credits.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HMT has published distributional analysis information on the impact of the Summer Budget 2015 tax credit measures on households. This information can be found here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/443229/PU1822_Distributional_Analysis.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/443229/PU1822_Distributional_Analysis.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The government is focusing the tax credits system on those who need it most. Prior to 2010, 9 out of 10 families with children in the UK were eligible for tax credits The measures announced in the Summer Budget 2015 will result in 5 out of 10 UK families being eligible for tax credits support.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The number of affected households and total reduction in credits to households in Scotland is not available.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC publishes information on families’ tax credit award within Scotland. The most recent available data is for 2013-14 and can be found here on gov.uk.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390683/answer",,,,,"7595 ; 7732","2015-07-21T15:59:59.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390683/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390683/answer",,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-16","Welfare Tax Credits: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the number of households in Scotland which will experience a reduction in tax credits as a result of measures announced in the Summer Budget 2015.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","7652"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390684","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-23","<p>There have been no changes to the eligibility criteria to an NHS Tax Credit Exemption certificate.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390684/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-23T13:28:19.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390684/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390684/answer",,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-16","NHS: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will make an assessment of the effect on the (a) NHS budget and (b) Barnett formula of reductions in the eligibility criteria for the NHS tax credit exemption certificate.","false","Biography information for Owen Thompson","Midlothian","Owen Thompson","7609"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390685","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-21","<p>At the Summer Budget 2015 the Chancellor announced that the dividend tax credit will be replaced by a new £5,000 tax-free dividend allowance from April 2016.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>A tax information and impact note setting out expected impacts will be published alongside draft legislation prior to the changes being legislated in Finance Bill 2016.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390685/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-21T16:33:09.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390685/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390685/answer",,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-16","Dividend Tax Credits","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what information his Department holds on the number of people that received dividends of £5,000 or more in 2014.","false","Biography information for Owen Thompson","Midlothian","Owen Thompson","7599"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390686","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-22","<p>The following was raised from the sale of radio spectrum since financial year 2010-11:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial Year</p></td><td><p>Sale revenue (£)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>2,368,273,322</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>0 (to date)</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Ofcom may determine appropriate reserve prices for spectrum sales in future years and will advise Government on expected sale revenues as part of its preparations for spectrum auctions. Ofcom publishes an annual ‘Section 400 Account Licence Fees and Penalties Account’ which details spectrum fees arising from Wireless Telegraphy Act licences. Their most recent report can be found at <a href="http://www.ofcom.org.uk/content/about/annual-reports-plans/1262041/annual-report-14-15/Ofcom_S400_2014-15_accounts.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.ofcom.org.uk/content/about/annual-reports-plans/1262041/annual-report-14-15/Ofcom_S400_2014-15_accounts.pdf</a>.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390686/answer",,,,,,"2015-07-22T15:12:58.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390686/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390686/answer",,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-16","Radio Frequencies","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much was raised from the sale of radio spectrum in each financial year since 2010-11; and how much he expects to accrue to the public purse in such ways in each financial year to 2019-20.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","7641"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390687","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-23","<p>This is a matter for the Prudential Regulation Authority (PRA), which is operationally independent from Government.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The question has been passed on to the PRA. The PRA will reply directly to the Member by letter. A copy of the letter will be placed in the Library of the House.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390687/answer",,,,,"7617","2015-07-23T14:49:19.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390687/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390687/answer",,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-16","Banks: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, which firms have been granted a banking licence since April 1985.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","7642"
